This paper deals with computer vision and pattern recognition tasks, specifically in the context of satellite image change detection. The paper proposes a novel framework for efficient computation in deep kernel networks, which are a popular type of deep network in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the design principle of the reduced complexity networks, which involves a variant of the cross-entropy criterion, indicating a possible connection to machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with the issue of computational complexity, which suggests a possible connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with satellite images, which suggests a possible connection to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
